# ARDL short and long run simulation 

The investigation use the ARDL framework to examine the interaction of variables, taking into account both short-term and long-term dynamics. The long-run coefficient estimate is predicted by equation (7), which also confirms the cointegration of the parameters. It incorporates the ECT into the ARDL framework to compute short-term dynamic parameters derived from long-term estimates, employing an error correction term (ECT) approximation. The equation (7) represents the ARDL long run equation below.

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \Delta \mathrm{LCO}_{2 \mathrm{t}}=\beta_{0}+\beta_{1} \mathrm{LCO}_{2 \mathrm{t}-1}+\beta_{2} \mathrm{LGDP}_{\mathrm{t}-1}+\beta_{3} \mathrm{LAI}_{\mathrm{t}-1}+\beta_{4} \mathrm{LSMC}_{\mathrm{t}-1}+\beta_{5} \mathrm{LICT}_{\mathrm{t}-1}+\beta_{6} \mathrm{LPOP}_{\mathrm{t}-1} \\
& +\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{1} \Delta \mathrm{LCO}_{2 \mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}}+\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{2} \Delta \mathrm{LGDP}_{\mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}}+\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{3} \Delta \mathrm{LAI}_{\mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}}+\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{4} \Delta \mathrm{LSMC}_{\mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}} \\
& +\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{5} \Delta \mathrm{LICT}_{\mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}}+\sum_{\mathrm{i}=1}^{\mathrm{m}} \alpha_{6} \Delta \mathrm{LPOP}_{\mathrm{t}-\mathrm{i}}+\Omega \mathrm{ECT}_{\mathrm{t}-1}+\varepsilon_{\mathrm{t}}
\end{aligned}
$$

where $\Omega$ represents the coefficient of the ECT.
